title: Bug 4121: JarExporter causes out of Sync
description: Bug 4121: JarExporter causes out of Sync
OB: If you export a directory (project) and place the exported JAR file in the same directory (project), then when you overwrite the exported JAR file for the second time, you will receive an out of sync message.
SR:
1. Open the project.
2. Export the directory as a JAR file.
3. Save the exported JAR file in the same directory as the project.
4. Overwrite the exported JAR file by exporting the directory again.
5. Observe the out of sync message.
